Achiever.description: Achievers have a great deal of stamina and work hard to reach their goals. They take satisfaction from being productive.

Activator.description: Activators can make things happen by turning thoughts into action. They are often impatient for results.

Adaptability.description: People strong in Adaptability prefer to go with the flow. They tend to be flexible and stay in the moment.

Analytical.description: Analytical individuals search for reasons and causes. They have the ability to think about all the factors that might affect a situation.

Arranger.description: Arrangers can organize, but they also have a flexibility that complements this ability. They like to figure out how all of the pieces and resources can be arranged for maximum productivity.

Belief.description: People with strong Belief have certain core values that are unchanging. Out of these values emerges a defined purpose for their lives.

Command.description: Command individuals have presence. They can take control of a situation and make decisions.

Communication.description: People with strong Communication generally find it easy to put their thoughts into words. They are good conversationalists and presenters.

Competition.description: People with Competition are best motivated by performance. They strive to win first place and revel in contests.

Connectedness.description: Connectedness individuals believe in the links among all things. They believe there are few coincidences and that almost every event has a reason.

Consistency.description: People with strong Consistency are keen to treat people the same by setting up clear rules and adhering to them.

Context.description: Context individuals enjoy thinking about the past. They understand the present by researching its history.

Deliberative.description: Deliberative people are careful and vigilant. They anticipate the obstacles.

Developer.description: People with Developer recognize and cultivate the potential in others. They spot the signs of each small improvement and derive satisfaction from these improvements.

Discipline.description: People with Discipline enjoy routine and structure. Their world is best described by the order they create.

Empathy.description: Empathy individuals can sense the feelings of other people by imagining themselves in others' lives or situations.

Focus.description: People with Focus can take direction, follow through, and make the corrections necessary to stay on track. They prioritize, then act.

Futuristic.description: People with Futuristic are inspired by the future and what could be. They energize others with their visions of the future.

Harmony.description: Harmony individuals look for consensus. They donâ€™t enjoy conflict and prefer to seek areas of agreement.

Ideation.description: People with Ideation are fascinated by ideas. They are able to find connections between seemingly disparate phenomena.

Includer.description: Includers accept others. They show awareness of those who feel left out and make an effort to include them.

Individualization.description: People with Individualization are intrigued by the unique qualities of each person. They have a gift for figuring out how people who are different can work together productively.

Input.description: People with Input have a craving to know more. Often they like to collect and archive all kinds of information.

Intellection.description: Intellection individuals are characterized by their intellectual activity. They are introspective and appreciate intellectual discussions.

Learner.description: Learners have a great desire to learn and continuously improve. The process, more than the outcome, excites them.

Maximizer.description: Maximizers focus on strengths as a way to stimulate personal and group excellence. They seek to transform something strong into something superb.

Positivity.description: People with Positivity have an enthusiasm that is contagious. They are upbeat and can get others excited about what they are going to do.

Relator.description: Relators enjoy close relationships with others. They find deep satisfaction in working hard with friends to achieve a goal.

Responsibility.description: People with Responsibility take psychological ownership of what they say they will do. They are committed to stable values such as honesty and loyalty.

Restorative.description: Restorative individuals are adept at dealing with problems. They are good at figuring out what is wrong and resolving it.

Self-Assurance.description: People with Self-Assurance feel confident in their ability to manage their own lives. They possess an inner compass that gives them confidence in their decisions.

Significance.description: Significance individuals want to make a big impact. They are independent and prioritize projects based on how much influence they will have on their organization or people around them.

Strategic.description: Strategic people create alternative ways to proceed. Faced with any given scenario, they can quickly spot the relevant patterns and issues.

Woo.description: Woo stands for Winning Others Over. People with this strength love the challenge of meeting new people and getting them to like them.

Default.description: This is a default icon for unassigned strengths.

Leadership.description: Leadership individuals are skilled at influencing others and guiding groups toward goals.
